Jukebox -

"Design a musical jukebox using object oriented principles"

A jukebox has the following features -

- CD's that it can be selected to be played.
- A start button to begin the selected track.
- A volume control.
- A coin slot.

Step 1 - Handle Ambiguity

- How old is this jukebox, is it a classical one or modern.
- Would it take CD's or records, this mainly drives the name of the objects
- Would the CD's be placed or ordered into categories.

Step 2 - Define the core objects